Exploratory Data Analysis¶

.describe(), .isnull() e.t.c among many other methods used in pandas to perform exploratory data analysis was also applied to the wrangled data. I was able to get statistical facts about my data. Some of these facts include:

  • the average rating for each dog is 10.8
  • The maximum retweet count for a tweet_id is a wholesome 70839 while the maximum favourite count for a dog tweet id is about 145k
  • the average confidence level of prediction algorithm 1 is the highest of all prediction algorithms with 0.60

Comparing the performance of algorithm's predictions(p1,p2 and p3). How did each fair?¶

Given that the image of each dog was ran through a neural network to predict if the image is a dog or not and also to return the confidence of each prediction and its percieved breed

here, i analysed and compare the three predictions and how they differ. Firstly, i defined a function to plot dog breeds where the number of dog breeds predicted has more than 20 occurences for each predition ,that is, where the prediction is truly a dog

below are the results of this analysis, where i was able to know how each prediction faired

You will quickly notice the difference in the number of dog breeds in each visuals. Now, thats how the prediction faired. The 3rd predictions have lower level of confidence compared to the first and second one
